    en: "A NY driver abstract is the official record of a person's driving history maintained by the Department of Motor Vehicles under NY Vehicle and Traffic Law § 202. It shows license status, license class, license expiration, accidents, traffic convictions, suspensions, and revocations. Employers, insurance carriers, courts, and rental car agencies routinely require an abstract. Drivers can order their own through DMV's online MyDMV portal, by mail using Form MV-15, or in person at any DMV office. Cost is $7 for the standard 4-year abstract or $10 for the lifetime abstract."
